=>Apache maven intro.
=================
Apache Maven: it is Build Automation Tool used to automate the build process of java applications.

- tool that helps developes to create , build, test, package and deploy apps automatically.

-open-source project managment and build automation tool developed by Apache s/w foundation.

- Maven is developed by using java lanaguage.
-we can use it with Spring boot, Spring , servlet, core java apps.

Build:
====
we write java code, several steps before it comes an executes application.


write code-->  compile  (byte code) --> run test cases  -->create jar/war --> deploy appln --> run on server

--this complete process is called as build process.


Manual Build Process:
=================
We create online banking app.
without maven..    we have to do all above things manually.

write code-->  compile  (byte code) javac *.java--> run test cases  -->create jar/war --> deploy appln --> run on server


Build Automation:
==============
Instead of doing everything manually, Maven performs everything automatically.

Maven introduced Standard Directory structure...




What we can do by using maven tool?
============================

1. we can create standard project structure.

2. Download required libraries. (spring, hibernate, redis, thymeleaf, web, dta jpa , kafka)

3. Compile source code of the project.

4. run unit test cases.

5. package our app in the form of jar/war.

6. easy CI/CD tool integration.


=> standalone apps will be package as jar file..  (apps which executes from main() method)
=> web apps will be packages as war file. (war)

to simplifuy java project build process.



Maven setup in windows.
===================
to setup maven in our machine..    

-need java and maven installed.
-set path for java and maven.

Step 1:  install java, set path for path and JAVA_HOME (in ENV variables)

			path=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-21.0.11\bin

			JAVA_HOME= C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-21.0.11

			verify:  $ java -version

Step 2: Download maven s/w as zip file & extract zp file.

			https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi

step 3: move maven folder into C drive (optional)

step 4: set path + MAVEN_HOME (into ENV variables)

		path=C:\Program Files\Apache\Maven\apache-maven-3.9.16\bin

		MAVEN_HOME= C:\Program Files\Apache\Maven\apache-maven-3.9.16

		verify: $ mvn -v

=>Maven Terminology.
==================

1. Archetype :  Type of project which we want to create using maven

		quick-start : stand-alone apps
		web-app: web apps

2. groupId:  it represent company name (which org developing this project)

	eg.  in.dna, in.infe, com.google

3. artifactId:  project name

4. version.  current version of your project.

 		-SNAPSHOT  (under developemtnent /beta)
 		-RELEASE	(production release)

5. package ::  jar/war

6. Goals:  Goals are used to perform project build process.

	-clean  : delete the target folder
	-install
	-package
	-deploy
	-test
	-validate
	-compile -  compile source code and genrate .class files in target folder

7. Dependencies:  libraries/jar required for project development.

8. Repositories:  Localtion where jars are stored.

	Central Repo
	Remote Repo
	Local Repo

9. POM.xml

	Project Object Model.   it is xml file (maven project config file)

10. plugins.   it is an extension that does actual work during build.

			- maven-clean-plugin 	: deletes target folder
			- maven-compiler-plugin : compiles java code	
			- maven-surefire-plugin : run junit test cases
			- maven-jar-plugin 		: create jar file
			- maven-war-plugin		: create war file	


